        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 13 at 12:00PM CDT by NWS Chicago IL</headline>
        <description>At 1159 AM CDT, the public reported a strong thunderstorm near
Manteno, moving southeast at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 30 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Public.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Papineau, St. Anne, Chebanse, Martinton, Bradley, Herscher, Kankakee,
Beecher, Limestone, Crescent City, Irwin, Hopkins Park, Essex,
Beaverville, Sun River Terrace, Grant Park, Ashkum, Bonfield, Union
Hill, Donovan, Manteno, Clifton, Aroma Park, Momence, and Peotone.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
